Claims What is claimed is: 1. A stoma valve appliance, comprising: a base having an outer side and an inner skin-facing side configured to be secured to a patient over a stoma, the base defining a flow path between having an inner opening on the inner side of the base and an outer opening on the outer side of the base; a gate valve slidable between an open position and a closed position to control flow through said flow path; a stem with an inlet at a distal end and an outlet at a proximal end projecting inwardly from the base configured to be received in the patient stoma, the stem proximal end communicating with the inner opening of the base to continue said flow path through the stem; a balloon disposed around the stem; a balloon inflation port disposed on the outer side of the base; and a balloon inflation lumen extending from the balloon inflation port through the base and along the stem opening in the balloon. 2. The stoma valve appliance of claim 1, wherein the balloon is configured to secure the valve appliance in and seal the stoma. 3. The stoma valve appliance of claim 1 or claim 2, wherein the balloon is disposed at the distal end of the stem. 4. The stoma valve appliance of claim 3, further comprising a second balloon disposed around the stem between the distal and proximal ends of the stem. 5. The stoma valve appliance of claim 4, wherein a first balloon at the stem distal end is configured primarily for anchoring the valve appliance in the stoma and the second balloon between the distal and proximal ends is configured primarily for sealing the stoma against leaks. 6. The stoma valve appliance of claim 4 or claim 5, wherein said inflation port and inflation lumen communicate with the first and second balloons. 7. The stoma valve appliance of claim 4 or claim 5, wherein said inflation port and said inflation lumen communicate with said first balloon and said valve appliance further comprises a second inflation port and a second inflation lumen communicating with the second balloon. 8. The stoma valve appliance of any preceding claim further comprising a valve disposed in the inflation port for sealing the inflation port and inflation lumen. 9. The stoma valve appliance of any preceding claim, wherein the gate valve slides in a slot formed in the base. 10. The stoma valve appliance of claim 9, wherein the gate valve has a deflectable side protrusion configured to be received in a pocket in a side of said slot to secure the gate valve in a closed position. 11. The stoma valve appliance of claim 10, wherein the gate valve has a handle portion with at least one resilient arm configured to bias the side protrusion into said pocket. 12. The stoma valve appliance of claim 11, wherein the at least one resilient arm of the handle portion includes at least one user manipulable tab to permit disengagement of the side protrusion from said pocket. 13. The stoma valve appliance of any of claims 9-12, further comprising a valve cover on the base over said slot to retain the gate valve in the slot. 14. The stoma valve appliance of any preceding claim, further comprising a patient attachment wafer removably securable to the inner side of the base. 15. The stoma valve appliance of claim 14, wherein the patient attachment wafer has a central opening sized to allow a protruding portion of the stoma to extend therethrough. 16. The stoma valve appliance of claim 14 or claim 15, wherein the patient attachment wafer is secured to the base by mating clips on the base and said wafer, at least one said clip being deformable to provide a snap-fit connection between the base and patent attachment wafer. 17. The stoma valve appliance of any of claims 14-16, wherein the stem has a length sufficient to extend through the patient attachment wafer to position the distal end of the stem within the stoma when the base is secured to the patient attachment wafer and attached to the patient. 18. The stoma valve appliance of any of claims 14-17, wherein the patient attachment has a skin facing surface comprising an adhesive material selected for attachment of the stoma valve appliance to the patient over the stoma. 19. The stoma valve appliance of any preceding claim, further comprising an effluent capture device configured to attach to the base, the effluent capture device comprising a pouch attached to a bag plate, wherein the bag plate defines an opening configured with a sealing surface to provide a sealed connection with the outer opening of the base. 20. The stoma valve appliance of claim 19, wherein the bag plate comprises: plural bag clips arranged around the bag plate opening configured to engage behind corresponding attachment tabs on the outer surface of the base whereby rotation of the bag plate when placed in contact with the base removably attaches the effluent capture device to the base, said bag clips and corresponding attachment tabs being spaced apart to allow operation of the gate valve; and oppositely extending arms configured for holding and manipulating the effluent capture device. 21. The stoma valve appliance of claim 20, wherein each said arm of the bag plate includes one or more tactile elements to facilitate patient manipulation of the effluent capture device. 22. The stoma valve appliance of any of claims 19-21, wherein the bag plate further comprises a projection around an upper portion of the bag plate opening projecting into the waste pouch to prevent obstruction of the bag plate opening by material of the waste pouch. 23. The stoma valve appliance of any preceding claim, wherein balloon inflation port comprises a luer-lock fitting. 24. A stoma closure system, comprising: a base having an outer side and an inner skin-facing side configured to be secured to a patient over a stoma, the base defining a flow path through the base between having an inner opening on the inner side of the base and an outer opening on the outer side of the base and plural attachment tabs disposed around said outer opening; a gate valve slidable between an open position and a closed position to control flow through said flow path; a stem with an inlet at a distal end and an outlet at a proximal end projecting inwardly from the base configured to be received in the patient stoma, the stem proximal end communicating with the inner opening of the base to continue said flow path through the stem; 

 a balloon disposed around the stem configured to secure the valve appliance in and seal the stoma; a balloon inflation port disposed on the outer side of the base; and a balloon inflation lumen extending from the balloon inflation port through the base and along the stem opening in the balloon; an adhesive wafer removably securable to the inner side of the base, the adhesive wafer having a central opening sized to allow a protruding portion of the stoma to extend therethrough; a waste bag plate defining bag plate opening configured with a sealing surface to provide a removable sealed connection with the outer opening of the base, the waste bag plate further comprising: plural bag clips arranged around the bag plate opening configured to engage behind said attachment tabs on the outer surface of the base, and oppositely extending arms configured for holding and manipulating the bag plate, whereby rotation of the bag plate when placed in contact with the base removably attaches the bag plate to the base, said bag clips and corresponding attachment tabs being spaced apart to allow operation of the gate valve; and a waste pouch attached to the bag plate around the bag plate opening on an opposite side of the bag plate from the sealing surface. 25. The stoma closure system of claim 24, wherein said balloon comprises a first balloon and a second balloon. 26. The stoma closure system of claim 25, wherein: the first balloon is disposed at the stem distal end and configured primarily for anchoring the valve appliance in the stoma; and the second balloon is disposed between the distal and proximal ends and configured primarily for sealing the stoma against leaks. 27. The stoma closure system of any of claims 24-26, further comprising a valve disposed in the inflation port for sealing the inflation port and inflation lumen. 28. The stoma closure system of any of claims 24-27, wherein: the gate valve slides in a slot formed in the base; 

 the gate valve has a deflectable side protrusion configured to be received in a pocket in a side of said slot to secure the gate valve in a closed position; and the gate valve has a handle portion with at least one resilient arm configured to bias the side protrusion into said pocket. 29. The stoma closure system of claim 28, wherein the at least one resilient arm of the handle portion of the gate valve includes at least one user manipulable tab to permit disengagement of the side protrusion from said pocket. 30. The stoma closure system of any of claims 24-29, wherein the oppositely extending arms of the bag plate each include one or more tactile elements to facilitate patient manipulation of the waste bag plate. 31. A method of attaching an effluent capture device to a stoma valve appliance, comprising: placing an inlet opening of the effluent capture device in sealing engagement with an outlet of the stoma valve appliance; positioning the effluent capture device with waste bag attachment clips adjacent to attachment tabs on the stoma valve appliance; and rotating the effluent capture device to engage the attachment clips behind the attachment tabs. 32. The method of claim 31 , further comprising opening a valve on the stoma valve appliance after attaching the effluent capture device and while the effluent capture device remains attached to the stoma valve appliance. 33. The method of claim 32, further comprising closing the valve while the effluent capture device remains attached to the stoma valve appliance. 34. The method of claim 33, further comprising, after closing the valve, rotating the effluent capture device to disengage the effluent capture device from the stoma valve appliance.
